救急患者のたらい回し、自治体病院の閉鎖、産婦人科・救命救急科・小児科に代表される医師不足等、地域医療の崩壊・疲弊を指摘する声は多い。医療の問題は、多数の関係者が各々の立場から問題点を指摘するため、問題の全体像を把握することは難しい。ましてや利害関係者の主張が明確に出る地域医療の問題は、感情論に陥りやすく、客観的な議論を行いにくい。 本授業では、地域医療の問題を（１）政策的な観点から理解する視野、（２）本質的な問題を見極める力（問題発見）、（３）実行可能性を踏まえた解決策の考案（課題解決能力）の3つの能力開発を目標とする。授業は、第1部 地域医療システム概論、第2部 医学概論、第3部 地域医療の問題の3部構成で行う。第1部、第2部は、第3部の地域医療の問題を議論するための基本的知識の習得と視野の獲得という位置づけである。第2部については、地域で働いている若手医師による医学概論（集中講義）も行う。

There are many voices to point out the collapse and impoverishment of community healthcare such as shortage of doctors. As its solution, increase in medical department capacity and the raise in medical expenses are suggested, but does it really lead to a solution to the problem? A great many people including not only patients, families and healthcare workers but also the administration, politician and medical care-related private enterprises are concerned with the medical problem. It is easy to point out a problem from a specific viewpoint, but it is difficult to grasp and understand the perspective and the cause of the essential problems that should be settled. Besides the problem of the community healthcare that the claim of the interested party is presented definitely is easy to fall into emotional logic and is hard to perform an objective argument. In this class, we aim for developing three abilities of (1) field of view to understand the problem from the policy-like point of view, (2) the ability to find out the essential problem (problem finding), and (3) the power to devise the solution standing on the basis of feasibility (problem solution). The class is conducted by three parts consisting of Part 1: Overview of community healthcare system, Part 2: Overview of medical science, and Part 3: Problem of community healthcare. Part 1 and Part 2 are positioned as the process to acquire the basic knowledge and the field of vision needed to discuss the problem of the community healthcare of Part 3. In Part 1, students have to acquire the knowledge and the field of vision needed to understand the medical care system. Here, students are required to do homework using the picture/video teaching materials etc. that have been prepared for, because students have to study the necessary knowledge in a short time. In addition, in Part 1, a theme of Part 3 will be announced and grouping of students will be executed. In Part 2, in order to deepen the understanding about the disease and patient, overview of medical science will be lectured by a doctor. This is a few and valuable opportunity to learn the medical knowledge in SFC. In Part 3, students will have a class discussion about themes such as the medical treatment in isolated or underpopulated area, the auxiliary reproductive medicine, the lifestyle-related disease prevention, and the end-of-life care, etc. Through all the classes, an active remark of the student is evaluated.

